This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=2628

This plugin improves Vim's support for editing R code and makes it possible to integrate Vim with R. This filetype plugin uses either screen (GNU/Linux) or python (Microsoft Windows) to communicate with R. The new functions are similar to what you can find in Tinn-R and ess mode of emacs.

MAIN FEATURES:


  * Syntax highlighting for R syntax.
  * Smart indentation for R syntax.
  * Integrated communication with R.
  * Omni completion (auto-completion) for R objects.
  * Ability to update the list of objects for omni completion and syntax highlighting to include all R packages loaded by the user.
  * Object browser (must be updated manually)
  * Ability to see R's documentation in a Vim's buffer (not on Microsoft Windows).


Screenshots and Debian package: http://sites.google.com/site/jalvesaq/vimrplugin


USE: Please, read the plugin's documentation.

